title: Prep Roundup, Sept. 30
text:
Little Cyclones place second at Waukee Invite 
The Ames girls’ cross-country team finished second on Tuesday at the six-team Waukee Invitational. 
Ames finished with 34 points, just three behind first-place Waukee. 
The four-fastest Little Cyclone harriers finished inside the top 10. They were led by senior Claire Dupuis, who finished second overall with a time of 19 minutes, 14 seconds. 
The Little Cyclones’ next meet will be on Thursday, Oct. 8, at Fort Dodge. 
Waukee Invitational 
Team Results 
1. Waukee, 31; 2. Ames, 34; 3. Roosevelt, 70; 4. Valley, 96; 5. Lincoln, 154; 6. East, 176 
Individual Results 
Ames: 2. Claire Dupuis, 19:14; 6. Jessica Rehmann, 20:02; 7. Katelyn Moore, 20:17; 8. Emily Rehmann, 20:19; 11. Ryan Weiss, 20:34; 21. Eva Hill, 21:32 
VOLLEYBALL 
The Green Mountain-Garwin volleyball team defeated Colo-NESCO in straight sets on Tuesday evening in Colo. 
The Wolverines beat the Royals (3-11) by scores of 25-16, 25-17 and 25-14. 
It was Colo-NESCO’s third-straight loss.
